<center><table width=75%>
<tr><td bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>
<center><strong>Eye of Zomm</strong></center>
</font></td></tr>
</table></center>
<table width=70%>
<tr><td>Mana:</td>
<td>30</td></tr>
<tr><td>Skill:</td>
<td>Conjuration</td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top>
Classes:</td>
<td>
<a href="/spells/magician.shtml">
Magician</a>
 (8)<BR>
<a href="/spells/wizard.shtml">
Wizard</a>
 (8)<BR>
</td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top>Items:</td>
<td>
<a href="/armour/head.shtml#singing_steel_helm">Singing Steel Helm</a><br>
</td></tr>
<tr><td>Buyable:</td><td>
Yes</td></tr>
<tr><td>Researchable:</td><td>
No</td></tr>
<tr><td>Drops from MOB:</td><td>
No</td></tr>
<tr><td>Cast Time:</td>
<td>6.00 seconds</td></tr>
<tr><td colspan=2><br></td></tr>
<tr><td colspan=2>Description:</td></tr>
<tr><td colspan=2>
Summons an eye for the caster to scout with.  If the eye is attacked the creature will come back for the caster.  Duration for the eye is 5 ticks</td></tr>
<tr><td colspan=2>
<BR>1 tick = 6 seconds<BR>
When a range of effects are given, it usually means that the effect becomes more potent as the caster increases in levels.
</td></tr>
</table>
<center><a href="/comments/spell_comment.shtml?spellID=364">Post a Comment</a>
</center><BR>
<center>
 [ <a href="/spells/individual/eye_of_zomm.shtml?spellID=364&page=1"> 1 </a> ] [ <a href="/spells/individual/eye_of_zomm.shtml?spellID=364&page=2"> 2 </a> ]</center>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Suhuy</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2001-02-21 17:18:28</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>  One other comment about this spell's usefulness: It boosts Conjuration. You have no idea how much it used to burn me to try to cast Halo of Light and have it repeatedly fizzle... since I purchased this spell, I have boosted my Conjuration and rarely ever fail at Halo of Light... If nothing else, it's good for that.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Name</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2001-03-17 17:41:41</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I don't think this spell was intended to be used for purposes of pulling.  I think it was originally designed for spying or scouting.  I recall a Dungeons and Dragons spell 'Wizard Eye' which I believe this spell was fashioned after.  I wish Verant would realize that you all find this spell useless, and it wouldn't hurt balance in the game if they were to just change it a little and make it better.  <BR>
<BR>
I suggest they make it invisible, give it Levitate (ever try using Eye of Zomm in the water??  It has NO swimming skill, thus it almost doesn't move!) or give it maximum swimming skill, and even give it SoW.  <BR>
<BR>
You can give it invis to just NPCs if you want to still let players see the eye, but I don't see any real reason why they need to see the eye.  Why can't it be EQ's answer to 'Clarivoyance'?  Then you can be on a PvP server and be like 'careful... it's possible that we are being watched!!'  Cool, huh?  Just wanted the invis on there so it will not aggro mobs, I guess it's fair to let players see it.<BR>
<BR>
But will that terribly unbalance the game?  I think not!  You can only have 8 spells memorized at any time, so a spell would have to be useful for you to dedicate a slot to it.  I think players would finally start using Eye of Zomm if it had sow, levitate, and invis to mobs/undead.  And maybe even swimming skill so you could explore places in underwater depths.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
